## 8. KEY IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

### Byte Order
Always use **little-endian** for multi-byte values:
```csharp
// Correct (little-endian)
BitConverter.GetBytes((ushort)0x0054)  // Returns [0x54, 0x00]

// NOT correct for FEnet
new byte[] { 0x00, 0x54 }  // This would be big-endian
```

### Checksum Calculation
```csharp
public byte CalculateChecksum(byte[] headerBytes)
{
    // Sum bytes 0-18 only
    int sum = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < 19; i++)
        sum += headerBytes[i];

    return (byte)(sum % 256);
}
```

### Invoke ID Management
Keep track of requests and pair responses:
```csharp
private Dictionary<ushort, PendingRequest> pendingRequests
    = new Dictionary<ushort, PendingRequest>();

private class PendingRequest
{
    public byte[] RequestData { get; set; }
    public DateTime SentTime { get; set; }
    public ManualResetEvent ResponseReceived { get; set; }
}
```

### Timeout Handling
```csharp
public byte[] SendRequestWithTimeout(byte[] request, int timeoutMs)
{
    ushort invokeId = BitConverter.ToUInt16(request, 14);

    var pending = new PendingRequest
    {
        RequestData = request,
        SentTime = DateTime.Now,
        ResponseReceived = new ManualResetEvent(false)
    };

    pendingRequests[invokeId] = pending;

    try
    {
        stream.Write(request, 0, request.Length);
        stream.Flush();

        if (!pending.ResponseReceived.WaitOne(timeoutMs))
            throw new TimeoutException($"No response for InvokeID {invokeId}");

        return pending.RequestData;  // Or stored response
    }
    finally
    {
        pendingRequests.Remove(invokeId);
        pending.ResponseReceived?.Dispose();
    }
}
```

